{"id": 5032, "title": "Ticket #5032: condor_q -dag <dag-id> should show all jobs in the dag", "description": "<blockquote>\nthe command\n\n<p></p><pre>    condor_q -dag &lt;jobid&gt;\n</pre>\n\n<p>currently shows only the single job identified by &lt;jobid&gt;.  Users are a bit surprised by this, especially when &lt;jobid&gt; is the id of the DAGMan job.\n\n</p><p>The -dag option should add an OR constraint that DagManJobID == &lt;jobid&gt; so that all of the jobs in that dag will also be shown.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Apr-29 10:25:25 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\nnote: Currently there is no single attribute that we could query that would identify both children and grandchildren of the dag.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jun-04 11:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/bde9062f337eecfb28fc15bec30b5ad331001412\">[44965]</a></span>: complete documentation <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5032\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5032'); return false;\" title=\"condor_q -dag &lt;dag-id&gt; should show all jobs in the dag\">#5032</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5052\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5052'); return false;\" title=\"condor_q should have a way to show only totals.\">#5052</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jun-03 16:45</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nChec